news.title: Dust pollution: Citizens urge BMC to monitor construction in Mumbai
news.para: Given that each of the 24 BMC wards in Mumbai has a strength of 250-300 employees, and in addition, a complement of temporary workers, it may be time for them to fan out and track big projects in their respective jurisdictions, say experts.

news.title: Ludhiana: Builders say e-portal for NOCs delaying deals, ask PUDA official to intervene
news.para: ​​A delegation of Punjab Colonisers and Property Dealers Association (PCPDA) on Monday met the chief administrator of Punjab Urban Development Authority (PUDA), which is the nodal agency for the portal, to discuss these issues.

news.title: Gurugram civic body examines information on 86,000 more properties
news.para: The data of over 1.5 lakh properties could not be collected as 92,065 were vacant plots and 60,730 owners denied to share information with surveyors.

news.title: Fire safety over cost: India's path to sustainable growth
news.para: Strict adherence to building codes and use of fire-retardant material must to safeguard lives

news.title: Registration of property in Chennai records a spike
news.para: Between April 2022 and January 2023, the city has registered a 40% spike in number of property registered, while the state registered a 30% hike compared to the same period in the previous fiscal.

news.title: Telangana high court junks ED petition on Karvy Realty
news.para: ED counsel argued that PMLA does not allow any such time for the accused as the adjudicating authority is under an obligation to pronounce a decision within 180 days on the attachments made by the ED authorities.

news.title: Residents of Delhi's Mehrauli wave legal papers, ask how properties are illegal
news.para: Gupta’s house is one of the hundreds to get the eviction notice from the land owning agency stating that it was forest land meant for Mehrauli Archaeological Park. DDA plans to clear 20 acres thathave apartments, independent houses and jhuggis.

news.title: Affordable plotted housing scheme suspended in Gurugram & Faridabad over high land cost
news.para: More than six years on, chief minister Manohar Lal Khattar ordered the suspension of the scheme in the two neighbouring cities, during a recent meeting with senior officials of the department of town and country planning (DTCP).

news.title: Promoters can de-register their projects: MahaRERA
news.para: However, according to the pre-requisites set by MahaRERA for de-registration of a project, the project needs to have zero allottees or no bookings.

news.title: IndusInd Bank invests Rs 140 crore in Sushma group's commercial projects
news.para: In a statement, the Sushma Group said on Monday that IndusInd Bank has committed Rs 50 crore to its commercial project 'Sushma Capital'. IndusInd Bank has committed another Rs 90 crore fresh funding for its another commercial project 'Sushma Pristine'.

news.title: Centre approves modifications, relaxations in norms linked to housing regulations: DDA
news.para: Delhi Development Authority (DDA) said the Union Ministry of Housing and Urban Affairs has "approved modifications/relaxations" proposed by the DDA in the Housing Regulations, 1968, which were issued under section 57 of the DDA Act, 1957.

news.title: CCI approves acquisition of commercial real estate assets by Nexus Select Trust
news.para: The proposed transaction involves the direct acquisition of 100 per cent shareholding of 15 entities and indirect acquisition of 100 per cent shareholding of two entities acting through acquirer REIT's manager -Select Infrastructure and Nexus South Mall Management.

news.title: Repco Home Finance posts net profit of Rs 80.76 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Repco Home Finance's consolidated total income stood at Rs 330.85 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 1.66 per cent from Rs 325.45 crore in the similar quarter of the last year.

news.title: Jaypee Infratech's net loss widens to Rs 601 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: During the April-December period of this fiscal, the consolidated net loss stood at Rs 1,825.03 crore as against a net loss of Rs 1,683.32 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Ansal Buildwell posts net loss of Rs 2.17 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Ansal Buildwell's consolidated total income stood at Rs 5.74 crore in Q3 FY23, a dip of 89.90 per cent from Rs 56.81 crore in the similar quarter of the last year.
